{{Infobox football biography | name = Aghilès Benchaâbane | image = | caption = | fullname = Aghilès Benchaâbane | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|9|13|mf=yes}} | birth_place = [[Tizi Ouzou]], [[Algeria]] | height = | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | currentclub = [[USM Annaba]] | clubnumber = 12 | youthyears1 = 2004–2005 | youthclubs1 = DC Boghni | youthyears2 = 2005–2007 | youthclubs2 = [[JS Kabylie]] | years1 = 2007–2010 | clubs1 = [[USM Alger]] | caps1 = – | goals1 = – | years2 = 2010– | clubs2 = [[USM Annaba]] | caps2 = 10 | goals2 = 1 | nationalyears1 = 2008 | nationalteam1 = [[Algeria national under-20 football team|Algeria U20]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | club-update = 00:00, 28 May 2011 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 00:00, 28 May 2011 (UTC) }} '''Aghilès Benchaâbane''' (born September 13, 1989) is an [[Algeria]]n [[Association football|footballer]]. He currently plays for [[USM Annaba]] in the [[Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1]].
==International career== In 2008, Benchaâbane was called up to the [[Algeria national under-20 football team|Algerian Under-20 National Team]] for a [[2009 African Youth Championship]] qualifier against [[Mauritania]].<ref>[http://www.dzfoot.com/fiche-3877.php Algérie (U19) 0-0 Mauritanie (U19)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120319003452/http://www.dzfoot.com/fiche-3877.php |date=2012-03-19 }}</ref> He came in as a substitute in the 63rd minute as the game ended 0-0.
