{{Unreferenced|date=July 2009}} {{Infobox saint | name = Belie Belcan | feast_day = | venerated_in = [[Dominican Vudú]], [[Folk Catholicism]] | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | titles = | canonized_date = | canonized_place = | canonized_by = | attributes = | patronage = Justice, protection against evil, protection against enemies | major_shrine = | suppressed_date = | issues = }}
'''Belie Belcan''' is a very popular [[loa]] within 21 Divisiones ([[Dominican Vudú]]).<ref>http://www.ezilikonnen.com/dominican/belie-belcan/</ref>
==Information== He is considered the patron saint of justice who defends people against evil and enemies within the [[Dominican Vodou|21 Divisions]]. He is considered very polite, understanding, and protective by his devotees. In [[Roman Catholicism]], he is [[Syncretism#Religious syncretism|syncretized]] with [[St. Michael: Roman Catholic traditions and views|Saint Michael the Archangel]]. He is said to work very well with [[Anaisa Pye]], a female [[loa]] syncretized with [[Saint Anne]]. Therefore, in Dominican households, one will often find images of Saint Michael next to images of Saint Anne.
