{{Infobox person | name = Inger Nilsson | image = Inger Nilsson 2015-2.jpg | imagesize = | alt = | caption = Nilsson in 2015. | birthname = Karin Inger Monica Nilsson | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1959|5|4|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Kisa, Sweden|Kisa]], Sweden | othername = | nationality = Swedish | occupation = Actress, singer, medical secretary | yearsactive = 1969–present | spouse = | children = | known_for = ''[[Pippi Longstocking (1969 TV series)|Pippi Longstocking]]'' | website = }}
'''Karin Inger Monica Nilsson''' (born 4 May 1959) is a Swedish actress and singer.<ref name=NYT>{{cite web|title=Inger Nilsson|url=https://www.nytimes.com/movies/person/52736/Inger-Nilsson|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> She is a former child actress. She is primarily known for her portrayal of [[Pippi Longstocking]] in the [[Pippi Longstocking (1969 TV series)|Swedish-produced TV series of the same name]] during 1969<ref>{{cite web | title=Inger Nilsson | url=http://www.sfi.se/en-gb/Swedish-film/Swedish-Film-Database/?type=PERSON&itemid=68765 | language=Swedish | publisher=[[Swedish Film Institute]] | accessdate=2010-01-25}}</ref> which was compiled, re-dubbed into Dutch and later also in English and many other languages, and released as two feature films in 1969. In 1970, she reprised her role of Pippi in two subsequent feature films. She currently works as a secretary in [[Stockholm]], occasionally taking small stage roles.
==Career== Nilsson was eight years old when she was cast as [[Pippi Longstocking]]. First, she did a TV series and then three feature films. After Pippi Longstocking she was trained as a medical secretary, but chose to pursue a career as an actress. Nilsson was, among other things, [[property master]] at Östgötateatern and acted in several plays.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.expressen.se/noje/inger-nilsson-inte-fatt-vara-i-fred-pa-45-ar/ |newspaper=[[Expressen]] |title=Inger Nilsson: "Inte fått vara i fred på 45 år" |first=Thomas |last=Kingdahl |date=23 December 2013 |access-date=3 May 2016 |language=Swedish}}</ref>
In 2000 the [[Switzerland|Swiss]] director [[Xavier Koller]] convinced her to take a role in his film ''Gripsholm'', based on a novel by [[Kurt Tucholsky]].{{citation needed|date=January 2014}}
Since 2007 she has been appearing on the German TV-channel [[ZDF]] as the forensic pathologist Ewa in the TV-series ''[[Der Kommissar und das Meer]]'' ({{lang-en|The Commissioner and the Sea}}).
In 2009, Nilsson was a celebrity contestant on ''[[Kändisdjungeln]]''.
==Awards== In 1975 Nilsson received a [[TP de Oro]] award in the "Most Popular Personage" category<ref>[[:es:Anexo:Premios TP de Oro 1974|Received in 1975 but referred to 1974]]</ref> for her role in Pippi Longstocking TV series.
==Filmography== * 1969 - ''[[Pippi Longstocking (1969 film)|Pippi Longstocking]]'' * 1969 - ''[[Pippi Goes on Board (film)|Pippi Goes on Board]]'' * 1970 - ''[[Pippi in the South Seas (film)|Pippi in the South Seas]]'' * 1970 - ''[[Pippi on the Run]]'' * 2000 - ''[[Gripsholm (film)|Gripsholm]]'' * 2015 - ''[[The Here After]]''
